# TDD & Testing Rules

## Skills & layered architecture

This repo pairs **TDD** with **layered, DDD-friendly boundaries** so tests stay stable when implementations change. Structural rules (dependency direction, where pure logic lives) are in **`.cursor/rules/03-architecture.mdc`** (section *Layered design*).

| Concern | Use |
|--------|-----|
| Red → green → refactor, vertical slices, behavior vs implementation | `.agents/skills/tdd/SKILL.md` |
| Clean architecture, domain boundaries, trade-offs | `.agents/skills/software-architecture/SKILL.md`, `.agents/skills/architecture/SKILL.md` |

**How to test by layer**

- **`src/lib/`** — **Pure** modules (e.g. `import/`, `register/` schemas, normalizers): unit tests on **inputs/outputs** only; no mocks of internal helpers. **Infra** under `lib/` (`supabase/`, server helpers): test behavior with boundaries mocked or integration-style as appropriate.
- **Hooks / server actions**: exercise **orchestration**; mock **external I/O** (Supabase, Resend, etc.) at the boundary, not inside pure helpers.
- **Components**: assert **user-visible behavior** (Testing Library); avoid coupling tests to private structure.

New work: choose the **owning layer** first, define or extend the **public surface** of that layer, then apply TDD at that surface.

## Strict TDD Protocol

1. **Red → Green → Refactor.** No feature code is written without a failing test first.
2. **Test file location.** Tests live in `src/__tests__/` mirroring the source tree. Name convention: `ComponentName.test.tsx` or `hookName.test.ts`.
3. **Coverage gate.** `npm run test:coverage` must pass before any commit: **≥90%** lines/statements on `src/lib/**`, `src/hooks/**`, `src/proxy.ts` (see `vitest.config.ts`). For the full tree (`components` + `app`), use `npm run test:coverage:full` and follow `docs/quality/coverage-scope.md` until thresholds can be unified.
   - **Never** add `coverage.exclude` entries for production source files **only** to make thresholds pass. If coverage drops, **add or extend tests** (unit, RTL smoke with mocked boundaries, or integration tests). Exclusions are only for **non-source** paths already listed (tests, types, `page.tsx` / `layout.tsx` entrypoints, etc.).
   - **New or changed files** under `src/lib/`, `src/hooks/`, `src/components/`, `src/app/` actions, etc. must ship with tests that keep the gate green.
   - **Out of scope for the coverage include list:** `src/types/**`, test harness files; `page.tsx` / `layout.tsx` remain excluded as RSC shells (behavior covered via child modules + E2E when added).
4. **Pre-commit policy.** The repo expects `npm run precommit` before pushing: `eslint`, `node scripts/precommit-verify.mjs`, **`next build`** (`npm run build`), then `npm run test:coverage`. A Husky hook should call this script; commits are not merge-ready if any step fails.

## CI and test quality (gates)

- **Vitest + coverage** — any PR that touches **product logic** (`src/lib/**`, `src/hooks/**`, server actions, shared utilities) must keep **`npm run test:coverage`** green locally/CI with thresholds from `vitest.config.ts`.
- **No “make it green” shortcuts** — do not delete, mass-comment, loosen assertions, or add `coverage.exclude` on **production code** solely to go green **without an explicit** PR decision (reason, owner, recovery plan). If a test reflects current business behavior, the failure is signal: fix **code** or agree a **contract change** and update tests in the same PR.
- **If a test is brittle** — refactor toward observable behavior while preserving intent; do not drop coverage without equivalent protection.

## Test Categories

| Type | Tool | Scope |
|------|------|-------|
| Unit | Vitest + Testing Library | Components, hooks, utilities |
| Integration | Vitest | Hook ↔ API interactions |
| E2E | Playwright (when added) | Critical user flows (login, enrollment) |

## Regression Analysis (`REGRESSION CHECK`)

Before editing code with existing tests, run a regression pass and **leave a note** in the closest test file:

```
// REGRESSION CHECK: Changing X may affect Y because Z.
```

- **New files** under `src/lib/`, `src/hooks/`, `src/app/**/actions.ts`, or shared logic: add at least one `REGRESSION CHECK` block in the test covering the main surface (which invariants or contracts must not break).
- **Actions with i18n messages**: prefer asserting against `dictEn` / stable keys (`actionErrors`, codes like `MESSAGING_UC_*`), not single-locale literal strings.

## Rules

- Mock external services (Supabase, Resend) at the boundary — never in the component.
- Prefer `userEvent` over `fireEvent` for realistic interaction simulation.
- Every custom hook must have its own dedicated test file.
